<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,522,1071]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,366,970,996]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Larval hosts:</emphasis>
The larvae are seed predators and seem to be restricted to only two closely related host plants, widowsfrill (
<taxonomicName box="[402,576,1008,1033]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stellata">
<emphasis box="[402,576,1008,1033]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Silene stellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) W.T. Aiton, 
<taxonomicName box="[794,1001,1008,1034]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Caryophyllaceae</taxonomicName>
) and fire pink (
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1390,1008,1033]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginica">
<emphasis box="[1197,1390,1008,1033]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Silene virginica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kephart, S. &amp; Reynolds, R. J. &amp; Rutter, M. T. &amp; Fenster, C. B. &amp; Dudash, M. R." box="[158,391,1045,1071]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="667 - 680" refId="ref30745" refString="Kephart, S., Reynolds, R. J., Rutter, M. T., Fenster, C. B. &amp; Dudash, M. R. (2005) Pollination and seed predation by moths on Silene and allied Caryophyllaceae: evaluating a model system to study the evolution of mutualisms. New Phytologist, 169, 667 - 680." type="journal article" year="2005">
Kephart 
<emphasis box="[262,321,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
